LU-19819: Fix lctl help messages

This commit fixes lfsck_query short help message.
Before:
    # lfsck_query --help
    check the LFSCK global status
    usage:
    lfsck_query [-M | --device MDT_device] [-h | --help]
                [-t | --type check_type[,check_type...]]
                [-t | --wait]
    options:
    -M: device to query LFSCK on
    -t: LFSCK type(s) to be queried (default is all)
    -h: this help message
    -w: do not return until LFSCK not running

After
    # lctl lfsck_query --help
    check the LFSCK global status
    usage:
    lfsck_query [-M | --device MDT_device] [-h | --help]
                [-t | --type check_type[,check_type...]]
                [-w | --wait]
    options:
    -M: device to query LFSCK on
    -t: LFSCK type(s) to be queried (default is all)
    -h: this help message
    -w: do not return until LFSCK not running

By the way, it alos align help messages by replacing tabs by space and have
a cleaner output.

Before:
usage: lfsck_start [--device|-M [MDT,OST]_device]
		     [--all|-A] [--create-ostobj|-c [on | off]]
		     [--create-mdtobj|-C [on | off]]
		     [--delay-create-ostobj|-d [on | off]]
		     [--error|-e {continue | abort}] [--help|-h]
		     [--dryrun|-n [on | off]] [--orphan|-o]
		     [--reset|-r] [--speed|-s speed_limit]
		     [--type|-t lfsck_type[,lfsck_type...]]
		     [--window-size|-w size]
After:
lfsck_start: start LFSCK
usage: lfsck_start [--device|-M [MDT,OST]_device]
                   [--all|-A] [--create-ostobj|-c [on | off]]
                   [--create-mdtobj|-C [on | off]]
                   [--delay-create-ostobj|-d [on | off]]
                   [--error|-e {continue | abort}] [--help|-h]
                   [--dryrun|-n [on | off]] [--orphan|-o]
                   [--reset|-r] [--speed|-s speed_limit]
                   [--type|-t lfsck_type[,lfsck_type...]]
                   [--window-size|-w size]

